436624913265,1.2356167930996171,1.758781841119871,1.1743433342288032,1.493689446683396],"id":180058,"name":"consumption_energy_intensity","unit":"","description":"Consumption-based energy intensity is measured as the number of kilowatt-hours used per dollar of GDP. This is measured in 2017 international-$, which adjusts for inflation and cross-country price differences.  Consumption-based energy adjusts for the energy embedded in traded goods: it is the energy used domestically minus energy used to produce exported goods; plus the energy used for imported goods.","createdAt":"2021-11-15T08:00:24.000Z","updatedAt":"2021-11-15T08:09:27.000Z","code":null,"coverage":"","timespan":"","datasetId":5403,"sourceId":21238,"shortUnit":null,"display":{"name":"Consumption-based energy intensity per dollar","unit":"kilowatt-hours per $","shortUnit":"kWh","includeInTable":true},"columnOrder":0,"originalMetadata":null,"datasetName":"Consumption-based energy (Kulionis, 2021)","s_id":21238,"s_name":"Calculated by Viktoras Kulionis, based on the EXIOBASE v3.8.2 database","source":{"id":21238,"name":"Calculated by Viktoras Kulionis, based on the EXIOBASE v3.8.2 database","dataPublishedBy":"Calculated by Viktoras Kulionis, based on the EXIOBASE v3.8.2 database","dataPublisherSource":"","link":"https://zenodo.org/record/5589597#.YYf3EdnMK_0","retrievedData":"","additionalInfo":"Consumption-based (trade-adjusted) energy use can be calculated from data published in the EXIOBASE v3.8.2 database using a multi-regional input-output (MRIO) model.\n\nThis MRIO model uses data on the quantity of goods traded, and the country-specific energy intensity of producing those goods to estimate the amount of energy embodied in exported goods, and in imported goods. \n\nConsumption-based (trade-adjusted) energy use is then calculated as domestic energy use minus energy embodied in exported goods, plus imported goods.\n\nThis trade-adjusted energy use data was calculated by <a href=\"https://baug.ethz.ch/en/department/people/staff/personen-detail.MjY1MDUz.TGlzdC82NzksLTU1NTc1NDEwMQ==.html\">Viktoras Kulionis</a> using this approach.\n\nThe EXIOBASE v3.8.2 database is available online: https://zenodo.org/record/5589597#.YYf3EdnMK_0.\n\nWe have calculated per capita metrics by combining this data with population data from the UN World Population Prospects: https://population.un.org/wpp/\n\nWe have calculated energy intensity metrics by combining this data with GDP data (measured in 2017 international dollars, which corrects for inflation and cross-country price differences) from the World Bank: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator\n\n"}}},"entityKey":{"1":{"name":"United Kingdom","code":"GBR"},"2":{"name":"Ireland","code":"IRL"},"3":{"name":"France","code":"FRA"},"4":{"name":"Belgium","code":"BEL"},"5":{"name":"Netherlands","code":"NLD"},"6":{"name":"Germany","code":"DEU"},"7":{"name":"Switzerland","code":"CHE"},"8":{"name":"Italy","code":"ITA"},"9":{"name":"Spain","code":"ESP"},"10":{"name":"Sweden","code":"SWE"},"11":{"name":"Poland","code":"POL"},"12":{"name":"Russia","code":"RUS"},"13":{"name":"United States","code":"USA"},"14":{"name":"Japan","code":"JPN"},"23":{"name":"Australia","code":"AUS"},"24":{"name":"Austria","code":"AUT"},"37":{"name":"Brazil","code":"BRA"},"39":{"name":"Bulgaria","code":"BGR"},"44":{"name":"Canada","code":"CAN"},"70":{"name":"Turkey","code":"TUR"},"81":{"name":"South Africa","code":"ZAF"},"83":{"name":"Slovenia","code":"SVN"},"85":{"name":"Slovakia","code":"SVK"},"92":{"name":"Romania","code":"ROU"},"95":{"name":"Portugal","code":"PRT"},"102":{"name":"Norway","code":"NOR"},"113":{"name":"Mexico","code":"MEX"},"119":{"name":"Lithuania","code":"LTU"},"122":{"name":"Latvia","code":"LVA"},"127":{"name":"South Korea","code":"KOR"},"136":{"name":"Indonesia","code":"IDN"},"137":{"name":"India","code":"IND"},"138":{"name":"Hungary","code":"HUN"},"149":{"name":"Greece","code":"GRC"},"155":{"name":"Finland","code":"FIN"},"156":{"name":"Estonia","